    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-27T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-27T13:00:00-05:00" n="718"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.51/8–1646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-27T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 27, 1946—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>612. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 880 Aug 16.<note n="42"
                        xml:id="d718fn42">Not printed.</note> Turk Embassy advised <gloss
                        target="#t_Eximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> approval exporter credits $25
                        million.<note n="43" xml:id="d718fn43">The Chairman of the Export-Import
                        Bank addressed a letter to the Turkish Ambassador on July 12.</note> Bank
                    informed by Turk Govt <pb facs="0924" n="912" xml:id="pg_912"/> division among
                    Ministries as follows: Economy and Affiliated Institutions 15, Communications
                    and Transport 5, Customs and Monopolies 4, Public Works 1. Details period of
                    time interest rate to be determined project by project. Turks were told interest
                    likely to average about three and half per cent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
